me-permission-request-permission-re\",\n144:         \"app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-util-e655d230ac-001-runtime-permission-request-permission-re\",\n145:         \"app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-ui-theme-shape-kt-a0991a3c9f-001-runtime-permission-request-permission-re\",\n146:         \"app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-ui-theme-color-kt-efec15826e-001-runtime-permission-request-permission-re\"\n147:       ],\n148:       \"resourceInputs\": [],\n149:       \"platformCapabilityIds\": [],\n150:       \"expectedTargetDomains\": [\n151:         \"entry/src/main/module.json5\",\n152:         \"entry/cjpm.toml\",\n153:         \"build-profile.json5\",\n154:         \"entry/build-profile.json5\",\n155:         \"ability_mainability_entry.cj\",\n156:         \"module_entry_entry.cj\",\n157:         \"app_ability.cj\",\n158:         \"ability_stage.cj\",\n159:         \"ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/startup/startup_launch_service.cj\",\n160:         \"ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/startup/startup_store.cj\",\n161:         \"base/profile/main_pages.json\",\n162:         \"ohos_app_cangjie_entry/data/session/login_preferences_service.cj\",\n163:         \"ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/route_registry.cj\",\n164:         \"ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/shell_route_state.cj\",\n165:         \"ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj\",\n166:         \"ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/login/login_store.cj\",\n167:         \"AppScope/app.json5\",\n168:         \"base/element/string.json\",\n169:         \"base/element/color.json\",\n170:         \"ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/app_router.cj\",\n171:         \"ohos_app_cangjie_entry/common/foodike_resources.cj\",\n172:         \"ohos_app_cangjie_entry/common/foodike_theme.cj\"\n173:       ],\n174:       \"requiredBehaviors\": [\n175:         \"HarmonyOS phase-01 build configuration likewise declares no permission-specific module wiring and keeps requestPermissions empty.\",\n176:         \"HarmonyOS replaces the Android application stack with stage-mode build descriptors plus explicit EntryAbility and FoodikeAbilityStage registration creators and lifecycle classes.\",\n177:         \"HarmonyOS replaces Android splash and Compose entry wiring with EntryAbility startup resolution, the shared bootstrapStartRoute runtime variable, a focused startup launch service, FoodikeBootstrap page loading, and the registered main_pages launcher page.\",\n178:         \"HarmonyOS replaces DataStore with LoginPreferencesService-backed ArkData preferences, while StartupLaunchService consumes that persisted login-state foundation for later startup routing.\",\n179:         \"HarmonyOS keeps the root build free of permission-specific wiring; the entry module also leaves requestPermissions empty and adds no permission package configuration.\",\n180:         \"HarmonyOS replaces that shared Android Gradle lifecycle foundation with stage-mode build profiles, module descriptors, and explicit EntryAbility/FoodikeAbilityStage registration entrypoints.\",\n181:         \"HarmonyOS likewise keeps root build configuration free of settings-specific wiring; persisted login preferences live in the entry session service instead of the root build file.\",\n182:         \"HarmonyOS replaces the documented Compose navigation shell with explicit route ids, route labels, primary action targets, bottom-shell visibility rules, and the FoodikeBootstrap launcher page that dispatches onboarding, login, home, history, cart, profile,...\",\n183:         \"HarmonyOS phase 01 preserves this absence by keeping requestPermissions empty and by not introducing a permission flow before any protected capability exists in the translated app shell.\",\n184:         \"HarmonyOS replaces that documented Android component lifecycle with FoodikeAbilityStage registration, EntryAbility creation, and launcher-page loading through module descriptors and creator entrypoints.\",\n185:         \"HarmonyOS replaces that startup lifecycle with EntryAbility.onCreate resolving persisted login state through StartupLaunchService and with onWindowStageCreate loading FoodikeBootstrap as the registered launcher page.\",\n186:         \"HarmonyOS replaces those Android observable primitives with focused Cangjie stores and @State-owned UI fields for startup, login, route shell, and persisted login-state propagation, while LoginPreferencesService preserves the persisted session toggle used b...\",\n187:         \"HarmonyOS replaces the Android manifest resource wiring with AppScope/app.json5 and entry/src/main/module.json5 descriptor fields plus base string/color resources for app label, icon, version, and start-window presentation; Android backup/data-extraction XM...\",\n188:         \"HarmonyOS exposes the launcher EntryAbility through module skills, then continues startup into named in-app routes through the focused route registry and bootstrap page dispatcher instead of Android intent navigation.\",\n189:         \"HarmonyOS entry module keeps requestPermissions empty because the source manifest does not request runtime permissions in this batch scope.\",\n190:         \"HarmonyOS replaces the Android application/activity pair with FoodikeAbilityStage and EntryAbility registered through module entry creator files and entry/src/main/module.json5.\",\n191:         \"EntryAbility.onCreate resolves persisted startup state and onWindowStageCreate loads FoodikeBootstrap, replacing MainActivity startup with HarmonyOS UIAbility lifecycle hooks.\",\n192:         \"HarmonyOS replaces Navigation Compose with explicit route ids and shell logic in app_router.cj and bootstrap_page.cj.\",\n193:         \"HarmonyOS replaces those Android version-catalog lifecycle dependencies with stage-mode build profiles, cjpm package wiring, and registered EntryAbility/FoodikeAbilityStage entry components.\",\n194:         \"HarmonyOS replaces those library pins with EntryAbility lifecycle hooks and the FoodikeBootstrap page registration path.\"\n195:       ],\n196:       \"acceptanceEvidence\": [\n197:         \"Replace broad endpoints with precise target functions, types, resources, or tests before closing the group.\"\n198:       ],\n199:       \"riskHints\": [\n200:         \"current evidence uses broad shell/root/whole-file endpoints\"\n201:       ],\n202:       \"matrixRows\": [\n203:         {\n204:           \"kind\": \"source-feature\",\n205:           \"featureId\": \"app-build-gradle-kts-329cf39b55-002-runtime-permission-request-permission-re\",\n206:           \"featureName\": \"Runtime permission request, permission result handling, or protected API access.\",\n207:           \"sourcePath\": \"app/build.gradle.kts\",\n208:           \"importance\": \"critical\",\n209:           \"plannedPhase\": \"phase-01-project-skeleton-resources\",\n210:           \"status\": \"not-applicable\",\n211:           \"parityLevel\": \"not-applicable\",\n212:           \"verdict\": \"complete\",\n213:           \"reasons\": [\n214:             \"not-applicable has source/notes explanation\"\n215:           ],\n216:           \"targetEndpoints\": [\n217:             \"entry/src/main/module.json5\",\n218:             \"entry/cjpm.toml\"\n219:           ],\n220:           \"tests\": []\n221:         },\n222:         {\n223:           \"kind\": \"source-feature\",\n224:           \"featureId\": \"app-build-gradle-kts-52a26dc1e9-003-android-platform-component-lifecycle-suc\",\n225:           \"featureName\": \"Android platform component lifecycle such as service, receiver, provider, or application.\",\n226:           \"sourcePath\": \"app/build.gradle.kts\",\n227:           \"importance\": \"critical\",\n228:           \"plannedPhase\": \"phase-01-project-skeleton-resources\",\n229:           \"status\": \"platform-replaced\",\n230:           \"parityLevel\": \"platform-replaced\",\n231:           \"verdict\": \"complete\",\n232:           \"reasons\": [\n233:             \"implemented with behavior, parity, endpoint, and verification evidence\"\n234:           ],\n235:           \"targetEndpoints\": [\n236:             \"build-profile.json5\",\n237:             \"entry/build-profile.json5\",\n238:             \"entry/src/main/module.json5\",\n239:             \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ability_mainability_entry.cj\",\n240:             \"entry/src/main/cangjie/module_entry_entry.cj\",\n241:             \"entry/src/main/cangjie/app_ability.cj::EntryAbility.onCreate\",\n242:             \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ability_stage.cj::FoodikeAbilityStage\"\n243:           ],\n244:           \"tests\": []\n245:         },\n246:         {\n247:           \"kind\": \"source-feature\",\n248:           \"featureId\": \"app-build-gradle-kts-0a842e752f-004-screen-lifecycle-entry-point-initializat\",\n249:           \"featureName\": \"Screen lifecycle, entry point initialization, resume/pause refresh, or teardown behavior.\",\n250:           \"sourcePath\": \"app/build.gradle.kts\",\n\n(Showing lines 1-250 of 4406. Use offset=251 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"schemaVersion\": 1,\n  \"generatedAt\": \"2026-06-27T05:14:03+00:00\",\n  \"phase\": \"phase-01-project-skeleton-resources\",\n  \"purpose\": \"Phase implementation-group verdicts generated after grouped implementation batches. Use this as a bounded group-repair queue before the normal phase coverage gate.\",\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"implementationGroups\": 13,\n    \"repairCandidates\": 6,\n    \"byVerdict\": {\n      \"complete\": 5,\n      \"partial\": 8\n    },\n    \"byPriority\": {\n      \"critical\": 8,\n      \"high\": 3,\n      \"medium\": 2\n    }\n  },\n  \"repairPolicy\": {\n    \"repairableVerdicts\": [","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"translation-inputs\\phase-group-verdicts.json","time":{"start":1782537255680,"end":1782537255719}},"id":"prt_f077ffafe0012QXTunJalFq0vl","sessionID":"ses_0f8802e21ffebqE7prHEHNyq2J","messageID":"msg_f077fd31200198V3nfc2lR7xWU"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782537255748,"sessionID":"ses_0f8802e21ffebqE7prHEHNyq2J","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_7ZNe8vKhgkj0AcD1E2WdERLB","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"D:\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\docs\\harmonyos-cangjie-translation-checklist.md","limit":250,"offset":1},"output":"<path>D:\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\docs\\harmonyos-cangjie-translation-checklist.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # HarmonyOS Cangjie Translation Checklist\n2: \n3: 面向 Android Java app 迁移到 HarmonyOS Cangjie 的阶段性检查表。它来自 Spendee 案例记录和后续构建修复经验，目标是在每个 `opencode-cj` phase 结束时先抓住高频编译/宏展开问题，再进入下一阶段。\n4: \n5: ## 使用时机\n6: \n7: 1. 每个翻译 phase 开始前，把本 phase 可能触及的条目加入 `opencode-cj` prompt。\n8: 2. 每个 phase 结束后，先运行完整构建门禁：\n9: \n10:    `<python>` 表示当前 Python 解释器：macOS/Linux 可用 `python3`，Windows 可用 `py -3` 或 `python`。\n11: \n12:    ```bash\n13:    <python> scripts/shared/reports/build_hap_report.py \\\n14:      --workspace-root <translation-workspace> \\\n15:      --target-project <target-project> \\\n16:      --phase <phase-name>\n17:    ```\n18: \n19: 3. 如果报告失败，把 `build-reports/<phase-name>/build-report.md` 和首个 blocker 交给 `opencode-cj` 修复当前 phase，不要先开启下一阶段。\n20: 4. 构建通过后，再进入运行时 smoke 或行为验证。\n21: \n22: ## 资源和字符串边界\n23: \n24: - 不要把 `@r(...)` / `AppResource` 直接当作普通 `String`。\n25: - UI prop 如果可能接收资源字符串，优先使用 `ResourceStr`，或在边界处做 SDK 支持的显式转换。\n26: - 不要对 `ResourceStr` 调用普通字符串方法，例如 `isEmpty()`；需要空态时使用独立 `Bool` 状态。\n27: - 迁移 Android `setText(...)` 时，确认 HarmonyOS 端有明确的状态赋值或可观察数据源驱动文本刷新。\n28: - 每次资源迁移后，检查 `string.json`、media 资源和实际 UI 引用，避免保留旧 placeholder key 或缺失 AppScope/entry 双层资源。\n29: \n30: ## Option 和控制流\n31: \n32: - 不要生成 Java/Kotlin 风格的 `Option.get()`。\n33: - 非 UI helper 中使用 `match`、显式 `case Some(...)` / `case None`，或当前 SDK 支持的安全访问 API。\n34: - UI 构建逻辑中避免直接让 `match` 分支裸露生成不兼容的 component 形态；需要时拆成命名 `@Builder`。\n35: - 启动/依赖注入状态建议拆成明确的 `Bool`、错误资源、服务 option 解包 helper，减少 `@Component` 宏失败面。\n36: \n37: ## 包结构和导入\n38: \n39: - 避免 root package 与 `pages` / `routing` 之间出现环形依赖。公共 route 类型优先放在 `routing` 或独立 models/helpers 包。\n40: - UI 文件中避免宽泛 `std.collection.*` 导入；它可能和 ArkUI 组件名冲突，例如 `Stack`。\n41: - 需要集合类型时优先显式导入或限定命名。\n42: - helper 类型如果会通过 public `@Component` 生成构造器暴露，确认类型本身也是必要的 public 可见性。\n43: - 不要把临时 template/cache 文件当成迁移输入；`.cache`、build output 和 diagnostic log 只作为诊断证据。\n44: \n45: ## ArkUI Component 和 Builder\n46: \n47: - `@BuilderParam` 优先传入命名 `@Builder` 方法，不要依赖未验证的 inline closure 或 trailing component block。\n48: - 自定义容器组件要按当前 SDK 支持的构造器/slot 形态实现，不能照搬 ArkTS 示例。\n49: - 校验 ArkUI named arguments 和 modifiers 来自当前 Cangjie HarmonyOS SDK 文档，而不是只参考 ArkTS。\n50: - 对 `@Component` macro 失败，先缩小到入口组件状态、构造器 public 类型、资源字符串类型和 `@Publish` 字段类型这四类高频根因。\n51: - 组件内部紧密相关的 owner state 文本可直接在 owning page builder 中渲染，避免子组件 prop 复用导致同会话文本不刷新。\n52: \n53: ## 状态和可观察集合\n54: \n55: - 路由和跨页面状态模型使用 SDK 支持的 `@Observed`、`@Publish` 和明确字段类型。\n56: - 需要列表变化驱动 UI 时，使用 `ObservedArrayList` 等 SDK 支持的数据源，并给 `ForEach` 提供稳定 key。\n57: - 不要假设 `ObservedArrayList` 是普通 iterator；辅助逻辑中用下标访问或 SDK 支持方法。\n58: - 跨组件变化的 prop 需要 `@Prop` / `@Link` / `@Watch` 等明确同步链路。\n59: - 对 primitive totals、余额、计数等关键展示值，保存/编辑/删除成功后优先执行明确赋值，避免只依赖持久化回读触发 UI。\n60: \n61: ## 测试迁移和验证\n62: \n63: - 源项目已有测试时，当前 phase 相关测试应迁移或改写为目标侧测试，验证翻译后的业务、数据、状态、资源或刷新行为。\n64: - 源项目没有测试时，应为核心可测试逻辑补充适量测试；源测试过少时，应优先补高风险行为测试。\n65: - 如果当前 SDK/模板不支持某类自动化测试，应保持代码可测试，并记录 deferred validation、替代验证方法和后续完成路径。\n66: - 不要为了通过构建直接删除、禁用或弱化已迁移/生成的测试；应修实现、修测试集成，或明确记录当前阶段测试限制。\n67: \n68: ## 构建配置和工具链\n69: \n70: - 完整 HAP 构建必须使用 DevEco Cangjie plugin 管理的 full SDK，例如 `~/.cangjie-sdk/<version>/cangjie`；standalone `~/.local/cangjie` 只能代表轻量 `cjc` / `cjpm` 可用。\n71: - 缺少 full SDK 时，应先安装/启用 DevEco Studio Cangjie plugin，再继续 full build gate。\n72: - 每阶段记录构建命令、失败阶段、首个 blocker 和已解决 blocker。\n73: - 常见阶段含义：\n74:   - `ohpm install`：依赖、registry、模板测试依赖或 oh-package 问题。\n75:   - `SyncCangjieResource`：资源生成、配置 schema、Cangjie build support 注入问题。\n76:   - `CompileCangjie`：Cangjie 语法、宏展开、包依赖、ArkUI API 问题。\n77:   - `PackageHap`：资源/loader/package 产物问题。\n78:   - `SignHap`：签名配置问题；未签名 debug HAP 通常可能只是 warning。\n79: - full build 通过前，不要把 standalone `cjpm check` 失败简单等同于 HAP 构建失败；两者依赖来源不同。\n80: \n81: ## opencode-cj 修复交接\n82: \n83: - `apply_patch` 失败后必须 read-back，因为失败可能部分落盘。\n84: - `L.map is not a function`、`apply_patch verification failed`、`Failed to read file to update` 要分开记录。\n85: - 长 phase 被打断或恢复时，先让 `opencode-cj` 检查文件系统当前状态，再继续，不要重复生成同名组件或服务。\n86: - 构建 blocker prompt 应包含：\n87:   - 当前 phase 名称。\n88:   - `build-report.md` 路径。\n89:   - 失败阶段。\n90:   - 首个 blocker message 和 location。\n91:   - 只修当前 phase blocker 的约束。\n92: \n93: ## Phase Gate 验收\n94: \n95: - `build_hap_report.py` 的 Markdown/JSON 报告存在。\n96: - 报告包含 command、result、failed stage、first blocker、warnings、HAP artifacts。\n97: - 如果失败，已有 `opencode-build-blocker-prompt.txt` 可直接交给 `opencode-cj`。\n98: - 如果成功，报告记录 full build gate 通过，且可把本 phase 的已知编译 blocker 标为 resolved。\n99: - 下一 phase 只能在构建通过，或用户明确批准带 blocker 继续时开始。\n100: \n101: ## Spendee 证据映射\n102: \n103: - `@r(...)` / `ResourceStr` 误用导致重复 generic inference 和 macro blocker。\n104: - `Option.get()` 在当前 SDK 下不可用，入口和服务解包需改为显式 `match`。\n105: - root/pages/routing 包循环会阻断 `CompileCangjie`。\n106: - UI 文件中的 `std.collection.*` 与 ArkUI `Stack` 名称冲突。\n107: - `@BuilderParam` 命名 builder 比 inline closure 更稳定。\n108: - `ObservedArrayList` 不能按普通 `for-in` 假设处理。\n109: - 同会话 finance totals 刷新最终需要 owner state、显式赋值和可观察列表配合，构建通过不能替代运行时刷新验证。\n110: - 如果 full SDK 在 Phase 1 就接入，许多 Cangjie/ArkUI 编译问题可以在引入当 phase 就暴露，而不是累积到最终构建。\n\n(End of file - total 110 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# HarmonyOS Cangjie Translation Checklist\n\n面向 Android Java app 迁移到 HarmonyOS Cangjie 的阶段性检查表。它来自 Spendee 案例记录和后续构建修复经验，目标是在每个 `opencode-cj` phase 结束时先抓住高频编译/宏展开问题，再进入下一阶段。\n\n## 使用时机\n\n1. 每个翻译 phase 开始前，把本 phase 可能触及的条目加入 `opencode-cj` prompt。\n2. 每个 phase 结束后，先运行完整构建门禁：\n\n   `<python>` 表示当前 Python 解释器：macOS/Linux 可用 `python3`，Windows 可用 `py -3` 或 `python`。\n\n   ```bash\n   <python> scripts/shared/reports/build_hap_report.py \\\n     --workspace-root <translation-workspace> \\\n     --target-project <target-project> \\\n     --phase <phase-name>\n   ```\n\n3. 如果报告失败，把 `build-reports/<phase-name>/build-report.md` 和首个 blocker 交给 `opencode-cj` 修复当前 phase，不要先开启下一阶段。\n4. 构建通过后，再进入运行时 smoke 或行为验证。","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"..\\..\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\docs\\harmonyos-cangjie-translation-checklist.md","time":{"start":1782537255741,"end":1782537255746}},"id":"prt_f077ffb3a001NJBBHtFxS0kne1","sessionID":"ses_0f8802e21ffebqE7prHEHNyq2J","messageID":"msg_f077fd31200198V3nfc2lR7xWU"}}
